<title type="html"><![CDATA[MMC5 pulse channels]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8767&amp;p=93297#p93297"><![CDATA[
Alright, I've answered my own questions.<br /><br />It does have envelope and length counters, they work the same as APU except the length counter runs twice as fast. $5017/$4017 seems to have no effect on them.<br /><br />Phase reset does happen like with the APU.<br /><br />Square channels are never silenced because of their frequency values, unlike the APU.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Thu May 03, 2012 7:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
